import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.scatterplot(x='X', y='Y', data=data)
    plt.title('What is the relationship between X and Y?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

```
import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='Y', kde=True, color='blue')
    plt.axvline(data['Y'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Mean = {:.2f}'.format(data['Y'].mean()))
    plt.axvline(data['Y'].median(), color='green', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Median = {:.2f}'.format(data['Y'].median()))
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of Y?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
```
